Ingo Molnar <mingo@chiara.csoma.elte.hu> writes:
> IKD triggered problems (likely bugs in previous GCC versions) if regparm
> was used together with -pg (GCC's function-prologue profiling extension
> calling _mcount).
This particular bug is still present in gcc and has to do with the way gcc
supports the older prof format (-p).
ftp://oss.sgi.com/www/projects/kernprof/download/gcc-patch
 has a patch to fix 
the regparm/-pg combination at the expense of breaking -p further.
